dct_title_s: Surveys of the Anglo-German Boundary Commission on the south west frontier of Uganda / by Lieut-Colonel C. Delmé-Radcliffe, M.V.O, 1902-1904.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot elevation. Depth shown by soundings. Includes: Latitude and longitude of points conected with the work of the Anglo-German Commission, Uganda. List of latitudes and longitudes of main triangulation stations. From "The Geographical Journal." vol. 26. Volume 26, no. 5. and no. 6 . A copy of this map and companion volume is available from RECAP. Call number: G7 .J6874 vol 26, July to December 1905.
